ongs mostly to Lewis.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Irving_Langmuir#cite_note-4\"><span>[<\/span>4<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> While at <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/General_Electric\" title=\"General Electric\">General Electric<\/a> from 1909\u20131950, Langmuir advanced several basic fields of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Physics\" title=\"Physics\">physics<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Chemistry\" title=\"Chemistry\">chemistry<\/a>, invented the gas-filled <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Incandescent_lamp\" title=\"Incandescent lamp\" class=\"mw-redirect\">incandescent lamp<\/a>, the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Atomic_hydrogen_welding\" title=\"Atomic hydrogen welding\">hydrogen welding technique<\/a>, and was awarded the 1932 <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Prize_in_Chemistry\" title=\"Nobel Prize in Chemistry\">Nobel Prize in Chemistry<\/a> for his work in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Surface_chemistry\" title=\"Surface chemistry\" class=\"mw-redirect\">surface chemistry<\/a>. The <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Langmuir_Laboratory_for_Atmospheric_Research\" title=\"Langmuir Laboratory for Atmospheric Research\">Langmuir Laboratory for Atmospheric Research<\/a> near <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Socorro,_New_Mexico\" title=\"Socorro, New Mexico\">Socorro, New Mexico<\/a>, was named in his honor as was the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/American_Chemical_Society\" title=\"American Chemical Society\">American Chemical Society<\/a> journal for Surface Science, called <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Langmuir_(journal)\" title=\"Langmuir (journal)\">Langmuir<\/a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-frs_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Irving_Langmuir#cite_note-frs-1\"><span>[<\/span>1<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p>","name":"Irving Langmuir","p